                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc>
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support>
                                    <p>A very thick plaque of compact grey limestone, with the upper edge cut to a triangular form (more crudely finished than the other edges). Intact on all four sides, with the edges covered in modern red paint. The rear is pecked. The surface shows some signs of damage and wear.</p>
                                    <material ana="#material.stone.limestone" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/66.html">limestone</material>
                                    <objectType ana="#object.plaque" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259.html">plaque</objectType>
                                    <dimensions>
                                        <height unit="cm">24</height>
                                        <width unit="cm">27</width>
                                        <depth unit="cm">10.4-9.4 (left to right)</depth>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </support>
                                <condition/>
                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout>
                                    <p>The text is carefully centred (note use of ligature in line 2 to support this?), the final line much smaller.</p>
                                    <rs ana="#execution.chiselled" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1">chiselled</rs>
                                    <damage/>
                                </layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote>
                                <p>Deeply carved, fairly broad letters with pronounced serifs. Use of ligature in line 2 (intentional, to make the cognomen shorter than the nomen above?). Use of hederae in line 3.</p>
                                <locus from="line1" to="line1">Line 1</locus>
